Problem Statement:
Given an array A[] of N elements. The task is to count number of even and odd elements in the array.

Solution:
public void countOddEven(int[] arr, int n)
    {
        int evencount=0,oddcount=0;
        for(int i=0;i<n;++i)
        {
            if((arr[i]&1)==0)
                ++evencount;
            else
                ++oddcount;
        }
        System.out.println(oddcount+" "+evencount);
    }
